Description: Ibanez Iron Label RGIR27E 7 string. It's very clean. I don't see anything wrong with it. Plays really well, and sounds like a monster. These pickups scream. Oh, and it has a kill switch.The RGIR27E is a seven string solid body electric guitar model introduced by in 2013. It was among the first guitars produced under the metal focused line. Like all the Iron Label guitars, it is produced in Indonesia. The RGIR27E features a basswood body with white binding bolted to a maple and bubinga Nitro Wizard-7 neck with a 24-fret rosewood fingerboard with white binding and no inlays. Components include an Edge Zero II-7 bridge, dual EMG active and a kill switch. Variants also introduced in 2013 included the (which is essentially the RGIR27E's twin, except with a bridge), the 6-string and its fixed bridge version along with an 8-string . A 28" scale length 6-string, the , was added the following year. The RGIR27E was discontinued after 2016. It was replaced by the .
